	%h3 Authorization

	%p All requests should include the following query parameters:
	%ul
		%li
			%code t
			= " - the timestamp as an Unix Timestamp Integer"
		%li 
			%code client
			= " - the public key"
		%li 
			%code token
			= " - SHA256 hash of the users secret key and the timestamp they generated the request"

	%p Any timestamp older than 2 minutes should be refused.

	%h3 List All Cat Facts
	%b GET    
	%code= '/api/v1/facts.json?page=:page&per_page=:per_page'
	%br
	%br
	%p
		Get a paginated list of cat facts.  
		%br
		%br
		%b Parameters:
		%br
		If page is ommited, it defaults to 1.  Replace 
		%code :page 
		with the page of results you want.
		%br
		%b Optional
		specify
		%code per_page
		to specify how many results per page, otherwise defaults to 25.
	%b Response Codes
	%br
	200: Successfully fetched them
	%br
	%br
	%b Example Response
	%br
	%br
	%pre
		%code
			:plain
				{
				    "page": 1,
				    "total": 1,
				    "total_pages": 1,
				    "facts": [
				        {
				            "id": 1,
				            "details": "All cats are lactose-intolerant",
				            "created_at": "2014-03-03T19:21:51.727Z",
				            "updated_at": "2014-03-03T19:21:51.727Z"
				        }
				    ]
				}

	%br
	%br
	%h3 Create a New Cat Fact
	%b POST    
	%code= '/api/v1/facts.json'
	%br
	%br 
	Example post body:
	%pre
		%code
			:plain
				{
					"fact" : {
						"details" : "All cats are lactose-intolerant"
					}

				}

	%br
	%p
		Adds a cat fact to the database.
	%b Response Codes
	%br
	201: Successfully created the fact
	%br
	422: Failed to create the item
	%br
	%br
	%b Example Response
	%br
	%br

	%pre
		%code
			:plain
				{
				   "id": 1,
				   "details": "All cats are lactose intolerant",
				   "created_at": "2014-03-03T19:21:51.727Z",
				   "updated_at": "2014-03-03T19:21:51.727Z"
				}



